    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Interesting. There's a `stornvme` error (NVMe storage driver error) at boot time (07:14:46 on 04/07/2026), and several `Resource-Exhaustion-Detector` warnings. No WHEA-Logger events visible in the recent log (but the BSODs from yesterday might have been cleared or are in a different log). The stornvme error is particularly interesting as it could relate to the ADATA SX6000NP NVMe SSD.\n\nLet me also check for driver issues and BIOS version.",
